obo:ECO_0007695  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2048  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: CPT1C is a multipass membrane protein (uniprot Q8BGD5 or F1LN46, mouse and rat) expressed in pyramidal neurons (not astrocytes) of the hippocampus (Figure 1A). CPT1C is unique from the other two CPT1 isoforms due to its brain-specific expression and localization to the ER instead of the mitochondria. Distinct from the other two CPT1 isoforms (which localize to the outer mitochondrial membrane), the brain-specific CPT1C isoform localizes to the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) in cultured hippocampal neurons (Figure 1C-1D). Immunostaining of GFP-CPT1C in these cells shows CPT1C is present in the cell body and dendrites (both shaft and spines, Figure 1B). Several other studies in heterologous cells confirm the localization of CPT1C to the ER and not the mitochondria.. Experimental description: Immunostaining: Cultured hippocampal neurons, not explicitly stated but I assume based on reading the methods section that wt neurons used in figure 1 were derived from mice (no description of other animals used). WT and CPT1C knockout mice: CPT1C+/- cells were injected into C57BL/6J blastocyst. Chimeric mice displaying >50% coat color chimerism were bred with C57BL/6J females to generate F1 offspring. The sixth backcrossed generation was used in all of the experiments.\n\nBiochemical fractionation: adult mouse forebrain\n\nGFP-CPT1C plasmid information: From PMID - 18192268 \"For pCPT1c-EGFP and pCPT1a-EGFP, rat CPT1c cDNA was obtained by reverse transcription-PCR performed with 2 μg of total rat brain RNA. The 2700-bp fragment amplified was cloned in pBluescript and sequenced. pEGFP-N3 vector (from Clontech, BD Biosciences) was used to clone the coding region of CPT1c or CPT1a, to create pCPT1c-EGFP and pCPT1a-EGFP, respectively. pCPT1c-EGFP and pCPT1a-EGFP plasmids encode CPT1c and CPT1a proteins fused to the N-terminal region of EGFP, respectively.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030176 replaced by GO:0005789" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5676-366X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9783-5183" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2048" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

